{
  "texts": [
    "• Source: Source of the email (e.g., personal or corproate inbox, LLM rephrase, CAES_08, Warranted SPAM Archive).",
    "• Year: The year the email was sent or collected.",
    "Emotional and motivational labeling in this study builds upon prior research that investigated how phishing emails evoke psychological responses influencing user behavior from Tóth et al.",
    "That work identified key emotional indicators-such as urgency, fear, altruism, greed, or perceived scarcity-through a combination of qualitative analysis and a validation questionnaire in which participants rated the emotions elicited by real phishing examples.",
    "These categories informed our annotation framework, as they represent common manipulation strategies used by attackers to prompt user actions, such as clicking malicious links or opening attachments [Tóth et al., 2024]."
  ]
}